      "title": "See also"
    },
    {
      "blocks": [
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "external_url": "",
              "href": "/docs/api/ops/arctan",
              "kind": "link",
              "target": "arctan",
              "text": "arctan"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " is a multi-valued function: for each "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "x"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " there are infinitely\nmany numbers "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "z"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " such that tan("
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "z"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": ") = "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "x"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": ".  The convention is to return\nthe angle "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "z"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " whose real part lies in [-pi/2, pi/2]."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "For real-valued input data types, "
            },
            {
              "external_url": "",
              "href": "/docs/api/ops/arctan",
              "kind": "link",
              "target": "arctan",
              "text": "arctan"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " always returns real output.\nFor each value that cannot be expressed as a real number or infinity,\nit yields "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "nan"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " and sets the "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "invalid"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " floating point error flag."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "For complex-valued input, "
            },
            {
              "external_url": "",
              "href": "/docs/api/ops/arctan",
              "kind": "link",
              "target": "arctan",
              "text": "arctan"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " is a complex analytic function that\nhas ["
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "1j, infj"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "] and ["
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "-1j, -infj"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "] as branch cuts, and is continuous\nfrom the left on the former and from the right on the latter."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "The inverse tangent is also known as "
            },
            {
              "external_url": "",
              "href": "/docs/api/ops/arctan",
              "kind": "link",
              "target": "arctan",
              "text": "atan"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " or tan^{-1}."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "title": "Notes"
    },
    {
      "blocks": [
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "Abramowitz, M. and Stegun, I. A., "
            },
            {
              "kind": "emphasis",
              "text": "Handbook of Mathematical Functions"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": ",\n10th printing, New York: Dover, 1964, pp. 79.\n"
            },
            {
              "external_url": "https://personal.math.ubc.ca/~cbm/aands/page_79.htm",
              "href": "https://personal.math.ubc.ca/~cbm/aands/page_79.htm",
